<p><a name="The_classic_work" id="The_classic_work"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Information_theory&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: The classic work">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">The classic work</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Claude_Elwood_Shannon" title="Claude Elwood Shannon" class="mw-redirect">Shannon, C.E.</a> (1948), "<a href="/wiki/A_Mathematical_Theory_of_Communication" title="A Mathematical Theory of Communication">A Mathematical Theory of Communication</a>", <i>Bell System Technical Journal</i>, 27, pp. 379–423 &amp; 623–656, July &amp; October, 1948. <a href="http://cm.bell-labs.com/cm/ms/what/shannonday/shannon1948.pdf" class="external text" title="http://cm.bell-labs.com/cm/ms/what/shannonday/shannon1948.pdf" rel="nofollow">PDF.</a><br />
<a href="http://cm.bell-labs.com/cm/ms/what/shannonday/paper.html" class="external text" title="http://cm.bell-labs.com/cm/ms/what/shannonday/paper.html" rel="nofollow">Notes and other formats.</a></li>
<li>R.V.L. Hartley, <a href="http://www.dotrose.com/etext/90_Miscellaneous/transmission_of_information_1928b.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.dotrose.com/etext/90_Miscellaneous/transmission_of_information_1928b.pdf" rel="nofollow">"Transmission of Information"</a>, <i>Bell System Technical Journal</i>, July 1928</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Andrey_Kolmogorov" title="Andrey Kolmogorov">Andrey Kolmogorov</a>(1968) "Three approaches to the quantitative definition of information" in International Journal of Computer Mathematics.</li>
</ul>
